source.name: System for Tracking and Administering Real-property (STAR) Lease
source.description: The System for Tracking and Administering Real-property (STAR) is the primary tool used by PBS to track and manage the government's real property assets and to store inventory data, building data, customer data, and lease information. STAR manages aspects of real property space management, including identification of all building space and daily management of 22,000 assignments for all property to its client Federal agencies.  This data set contains Lease and lessor detail information pertain to leases in active and excess buildings.
